content.description:
"Deceptively hard.  Good Rock and exciting holds" - from Maple Canyon Rock Climbing - 3rd edition.

Definitely a bit cleaner and more sustained than its neighbor to the right (The Joyful Toilet)
content.protection: About 7 bolts to a 2-chain anchor (shared with The Joyful Toilet on the right)
content.location: In the back alcove of the Trash Compactor, this is second line from the right (just left of The Joyful Toilet)

content.description: Climbing up this is no big deal, climbing down with a rope, pack etc is more of a problem.  Strongly recommend you thread the chains and rap down Ooga Booga.
content.location: Walk up the gully to the base of the wall.  There will be a clean black streak in front of you (Ooga Booga).  Look 15ft to your left and you will see some bolts.  Follow them up the 5-easy face to the ledge, then turn right and follow a ramp past a couple more bolts, the chains, and into the alcove.  You can belay kids or seconds up from the chains if they don't want to solo this approach.

content.description: Big cobbles all the way up.  Similar to it's neighbor on the left, minus the crimpy section.
content.protection: 7 bolts plus two for the anchor
content.location: In the back chasm, third deepest route on the right.  Shares anchors with I Dream of Porcelain.

content.description:
"These rivers of suggestion are driving me away."

A fun little jaunt on big holds.

Climb up the shallow chimney crack, past a low break in the wall, then break left up a low angle ramp.

Finish on steeper rock and gi-normous holds to a two bolt anchor.

Unknown how the anchors on this route have fared since installation.  Route, no doubt, sees a fair bit of moisture.  Take care and be mindful of rusty fixed hardware of dubious condition.

"The wise man built his words upon the rocks

But I'm not bound to follow suit

The trees will bend, the conversation's dimmed

Go build yourself another home, this choice isn't mine"
content.protection: 9 lead bolts to two bolt anchor.
content.location:
Route is located to the right of the approach pitch to the Trash Compactor.  Walk right and look for a ledge above ground level that's a 4th class scramble to gain.  Big enough ledge for several people.

Route starts in a shallow chimney crack groove (this crack continues all the way up the wall and gets wider with height.

Right of a dark water streak.

content.description: Starts with some low angle climbing for the first few bolts - easy, but still kind of fun.  The climb gets really interesting around the 3rd and 4th bolt.  Think creatively and look for the not so obvious holds.  Punch it to the top for a solid finish.
"One of the best 5.9's in the canyon.  Well protected" - from Maple Canyon Rock Climbing, 3rd edition.
content.location: This is the first (farthest left) route on the right side of the alcove in the back of the Trash Compactor.

content.description:
Climbs right around a faint corner to the face above, then left to the chains (shares anchor with "The Urinal" on the left)

Stiff 5.7 (partly due to the setting) and a bit dirty
content.protection: About 7 bolts to 2-chain anchor (shared with "The Urinal")
content.location: Farthest route back in the left corner of the Trash Compactor

content.description: Big cobbles to pull on until the last one or two bolts, where it thins out and earns it's grade.
content.protection: 7 bolts and two for the anchor
content.location: In the very back, second to last route on the right.  Shares anchors with Salty Biscuits.

content.description:
Located on the left, flat wall prior to the more slotty area at the Urinal.

From the shallow scoop, head up, clip shared bolt with Dumpster Love, then continue up past big chunky cobble to the more mossy looking terrain above.

A two bolt anchor awaits at the top of the wall.
content.location: Shares first bolt with Dumpster Love then continues up left.

content.description: This route starts low angle, then transitions to near vertical.  Last 3 bolts have some thin crimps and challenging moves, so keep moving. Nice climb, but the good stuff doesn't last too long.
content.location: Shares first bolt with Hobo Salad and then heads up right.

content.description: A nice route (fairly high first bolt) on fairly big holds, with a less positive crux up high. A bit mossy at the moment - will improve with traffic.
content.location: Rightmost on the N (right) wall, about 8' to the R of Salty Biscuits. There is currently a random bolt another 6' right of DAAGS.

content.description: Climbs the ice route/water runnel.  Runout, but a good'n for the kiddies.
